phase1.code:
using UnityEngine;

public class Conditionals : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        int health = 75;
        int gold = 30;
        bool hasKey = false;

        // Simple if
        if (health > 50)
        {
            Debug.Log("You are healthy!");
        }

        // if-else
        if (gold >= 50)
        {
            Debug.Log("You can buy the sword!");
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.Log("You need " + (50 - gold) + " more gold.");
        }

        // if-else-if chain
        if (health > 80)
        {
            Debug.Log("You are at full health!");
        }
        else if (health > 50)
        {
            Debug.Log("You are wounded, but okay.");
        }
        else if (health > 20)
        {
            Debug.Log("You are badly hurt.");
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.Log("You are near death!");
        }

        // Nested if
        if (hasKey)
        {
            if (health > 50)
            {
                Debug.Log("You can open the door and survive the fight!");
            }
            else
            {
                Debug.Log("You have the key, but you're too weak.");
            }
        }
        else
        {
            Debug.Log("You need a key to enter.");
        }

        // Ternary operator (shorthand if-else)
        string status = (health > 50) ? "Alive" : "Danger";
        Debug.Log("Status: " + status);
    }
}

phase1.explanation:
🎮 **Conditionals control the flow of your game.**

**`if` statement:**
```csharp
if (condition)
{
    // Runs if condition is true
}
```

**`if-else` statement:**
```csharp
if (condition)
{
    // Runs if true
}
else
{
    // Runs if false
}
```

**`if-else-if` chain:**
```csharp
if (condition1)
{
    // Runs if condition1 is true
}
else if (condition2)
{
    // Runs if condition1 is false and condition2 is true
}
else
{
    // Runs if all conditions are false
}
```

**Ternary operator (`? :`):**
```csharp
string result = (condition) ? "True value" : "False value";
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Conditionals are how your game makes decisions. Use them to check health, compare stats, and guide player choices."

phase2.brokenCode:
using UnityEngine;

public class ConditionalError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        int health = 30;

        // Missing braces for else
        if (health > 50)
            Debug.Log("Healthy!");
        else
            Debug.Log("Not healthy!");
            Debug.Log("This line always runs!");  // Not in else block!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Without braces, only the first statement after `else` belongs to the `else` block.

**The fix:**
```csharp
if (health > 50)
{
    Debug.Log("Healthy!");
}
else
{
    Debug.Log("Not healthy!");
    Debug.Log("This line is now inside the else block.");
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always use braces `{}` with if and else, even for single lines. It prevents this exact bug."
